'''Long:'''

 

Lili Fuhr is heading the Ecology and Sustainable Development Department of the Heinrich Böll Foundation's headoffice in Berlin. Before then she was in charge of International Politics. She focusses on International Climate, Energy and Resource Politics globally. Lili studied Geography, Political Science, Sociology and African Studies in Cologne, Tuebingen, Strasbourg and Berlin. She was born in 1980 in Cologne, Germany, has two daughters and lives in Berlin. Her interest in the Commons results from a recognition that a lack of participation in decisions on how we use and share our natural resources lies at the heart of the current ecological crises. In order to solve these we need to redistribute that power and give it back to those whose livelihoods depend on it. Lili has a German weblog (www.klima-der-gerechtigkeit.de) where she regularly comments on international climate and resource topics. 


